# Dropped at /etc/default/weston on the dev image only.
# Prod ships without this file, so the EnvironmentFile=- in the unit
# leaves WESTON_EXTRA_FLAGS empty and weston runs without --debug
# and without the VNC backend.
#
# --backends loads BOTH drm and vnc backends in the same compositor
# instance, so the panel keeps rendering normally and a VNC server
# also listens on port 5900. weston ignores the [core] backend= ini
# setting when --backends is on the CLI. The VNC output is configured
# via [output] name=vnc-output-0 in weston-dev.ini and uses clone_of=
# to mirror the DSI-1 panel content rather than expose an empty
# secondary output.
#
# --disable-transport-layer-security: plaintext VNC + no auth. Safe
# only because the device's only network is the private USB-CDC-NCM
# gadget link to the dev host. Prod images don't ship this config.
WESTON_EXTRA_FLAGS=--debug --backends=drm-backend.so,vnc-backend.so --disable-transport-layer-security
